snippet.title: Pudgie Wudgie's Greatest Moments
snippet.description:
A compilation of some of Pudgie Wudgie's greatest moments caught on film.  

Pudgie Wudgie 1986 - 2001 RIP

During Pudgie Wudgie's 14 years on earth, Pudgie and Frank brought joy and happiness to thousands of people.  Frank knew almost immediately that Pudgie was an exceptional cat.  What began as a few amazing tricks turned into a life of international celebrity.  Pudgie Wudgie appeared in the National Enquirer, live on the Maury Povich Show, in a taped segment on the David Letterman Show, and in a commercial for Dad's Cat Food. Pudgie appeared on television and in newspapers worldwide, as Italian, Turkish, and most recently Canadian media have taken an interest in his fascinating story.  Despite all this attention, during his life Pudgie always found the time to entertain at local schools, hospitals, and nursing homes in the Pittsburgh area.  Pudgie's affection for the Pittsburgh Steelers is also legendary -- many have seen his Steeler's Fan costume in the Western Pennsylvania Sports Museum at the Heinz History Center, Pittsburgh PA.

snippet.title: Ultra Cheap Movie Tricks and Practical Effects
snippet.description:
Yes, smoke and mirrors, literally! All kinds of cheap ways of tricking the camera without using computers, green screen or CGI effects... the Markus way. This is how they used to do it in the 80s and 90s. Well, at least I did, lol. Miniatures, forced perspective, glass paintings, foreground miniatures, multiplane shots, fishing line, foam core, hot glue, and all kinds of optical mind tricks to amuse and tickle your fancy. These cheap FX can still be used with video cameras nowadays for those lacking money but full of inspiration and the desire to experiment. This was all filmed in VHS so please excuse the quality.

snippet.title: Tango's Ultimate Horror
snippet.description:
Genuinely terrifying 1993 advert for Tango, rated PG, which pops up on a couple of rental VHS tapes from time to time.

An ugly, deformed orange monster throws what appears to be a webbed foot at a poor black man, scarring him for life. Then we see a gruesome close-up of his face, as he snarls at the camera.

Let me get this straight: you banned the totally average "Football" advert from being shown during children's programming, but you let this pass? It's scary. Kids would run away crying after seeing this. I know I did. It's the most horrific... creature Tango has ever devised. I know they make weird adverts, but this has to be the most disturbing of them all. It's equal to that Irn Bru ad with the possessed kid in the nursery. They're not right in the head.

snippet.title: Scraping Old Layers Of Wax From Surfboards | Art Insider
snippet.description:
Hogan Peters, founder of YEW!, walks us through how he and his team create sustainable surf wax bars made from beeswax. The wax is sourced from bee-centric beekeepers, melted down, and poured into cupcake molds. YEW! makes six different types of surf wax, including a basecoat wax, a cool wax, a cold wax, a warm wax, a tropical wax, and a soft top wax. The team has also gained an online following for its satisfying surfboard dewaxing and rewaxing videos.

snippet.title: Richard SImmons 'Party Off The Pounds!'
snippet.description: TIME LIFE AND RICHARD SIMMONS ANNOUNCE SuperSweatin: Party Off The Pounds® FAIRFAX, VA  December 4, 2008  Richard Simmons has been helping people lose weight and get healthy for thirty years with his unique enthusiasm, charm and encouragement. In the late 80s through early 90s, Richard developed the Sweatin to the Oldies series, one of the best-selling fitness videos of all times. First New Sweatin Release in 15 Years For fifteen years, fans have been clamoring for the next Sweatin release. Finally it is here -- Supersweatin: Party Off The Pounds, a brand new aerobic workout using Richards one-of-a-kind approach: real people dancing to real music, and having real fun. Supersweatin: Party Off The Pounds makes exercise fun with 50 minutes of aerobic dance set to ten chart-topping hits from the 80s, including: I Wanna Dance With Somebody, Hit Me With Your Best Shot, If I Could Turn Back Time, Mickey and more! Appropriate for all fitness levels, Party Off The Pounds is one party not to miss. Supersweatin: Party Off The Pounds will be available at retail December 30, 2008, just in time to dance away those holiday pounds

snippet.title: Tom Segura - Scared Straight
snippet.description:
Tom Segura talks about this episode of Scared Straight.

Original Link:
 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XfqMvdqPXeE&t=1s

Thought that I would change it up today. 

Based on the multiple award-winning documentary "Scared Straight!" from executive producer Arnold Shapiro, "Beyond Scared Straight," much like the original, profiles unique juvenile crime prevention programs in prisons across the U.S. Each hour-long episode follows a handful of at-risk teenagers as they attend a program, which includes an intensive one-day session in a prison. A month later, the teens are asked what, if any, lasting impressions the program had on them. Some change their ways following the experience while others continue down the same path they were on before.

snippet.title: Reading Rainbow (Extended tv series theme song, sung by Tina Fabrique)
snippet.description:
I scoured the interwebs looking to find a top quality clip of this well-loved PBS tv series hosted by LeVar Burton.  I was unable to find one.  So I decided to make it myself.

The ideal would be a full-length theme song.  I've never heard that one has ever been made.  So I made that myself as well, here.  It would have been much better to have Tina Fabrique singing a second & third verse.  But without having that, I used what's available.

Tina sings a short acapella version here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8-EkXxQ1dJg&t=1m8s
...and this audio clip was used as a bridge to repeats of the chorus.

The visuals have been extended by plugging in the last version of the tv intro.  As I understand it, it was a version which was first used ~2000.

I hope a proper full-length song was recorded.  With extra verses.  And that it's just hiding somewhere.  If that exists, and ever comes to light, then we can look at remaking this music video.

Copyright belongs to the owner of the song and the visuals.  I do not own anything here.

The regular one minute tv intro is here:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hw_WV6Cg_Ys
It is the best quality version that I am aware of.

snippet.title: Slow Bob In The Lower Dimensions
snippet.description:
Written and directed by Henry Selick, this is the pilot episode of what should have been a series. It uses live action, stop motion and cut-out animation.

Bob is a strange guy: kind of a loser in the ordinary (?) world, a slow loser, he becomes a hero in the lower dimensions.

The following episodes were scripted but never went into production. Tim Burton brought back to life The Nightmare Before Christmas project, and Selick was asked to direct it. And you should know what he did...

The short runs five minutes, but it is introduced (and followed) by some brief commentary by the director providing the informations I wrote in this post.
UPDATE: I've posted an MPEG-4 version with no commentaries to play it inline.

Soundtrack by The Residents.

You might be aware of it by now, but Henry Selick is working at Laika Studio on a feature lenght movie based on Neil Gaiman's Coraline.

snippet.title: Tampa Police Spokesperson on Fake Sign Language Interpreter: ‘I Let Her In’
snippet.description:
More from Inside Edition: https://www.youtube.com/user/cbstvdinsideedition?sub_confirmation=1
Another sign-language interpreter is accused of signing total gibberish. This time it was at the police news conference announcing an arrest in the Tampa serial killings. A woman standing off to the side was supposedly translating every word, but it turns out much of what she was signing was nonsense. The woman, identified as Derlyn Roberts, has a string of arrests for fraud. So how did she come to be "translating" at last week's high-profile police news conference? #InsideEdition

snippet.title: The Komodo Dragon Eating Everything In Sight
snippet.description:
Komodo dragons are the world's largest living lizards, and they have some fascinating skills and characteristics that might pique your interest. However, for your own protection, it's best to learn about them from videos rather than seeing them in person. You're in for a treat if you've never seen a Komodo attack its prey before; trust me. It is not pretty, so I’m warning you, but if you like gore, then you’re at the right place as we look at the Komodo dragon eating everything in sight.

► Subscribe For New Videos! ► shorturl.at/krBX9 

Watch our “15 Craziest Animal Battles Caught On Camera”
video here: https://youtu.be/JM4ihgEXXGQ
Watch our “How Squirrels Hunt And Survive In The Wild”
video here: https://youtu.be/ONLpyHpxn88
Watch our “15 Startling Moments Of Snakes Messing With The Wrong Opponent”
video here:https://youtu.be/511_8gBuuHA

Komodo VS Deer

This poor deer was trying to enjoy a day at the beach when a Komodo dragon forgot his lunch at home. So, guess what? The dragon decided to borrow the deer to fill in for his lunch. You can see the Komodo’s digging inside the deer’s belly to pull chunks of meat out of there. The deer is dead, but it wasn’t when they began eating.  Komodo dragons are more active in the morning because Komodo dragons are cold-blooded animals. Usually, during the rainy season, deer are more active and present at beaches. This deer was trying to enjoy a moment at the beach when a couple of Komodo lifeguards tried to save it from the water, so they could eat it.  A male Komodo monitors a deer that had been injured by a bite a few days earlier and continues to follow the deer. When the deer begins to get sick from the bacterial infection, the Komodo decides it’s time to kill and eat the deer. The deer tries running away, but the Komodo remains latched on to it. A small Komodo approaches a young deer, and the deer tries stomping on the Komodo when another Komodo shows up and they corner the deer. A larger animal standing there doesn’t even pay attention to the two Komodo’s. The small deer hides behind the big animal, so the Komodo’s don’t get close to it, but how long is that going to last? 

Komodo VS Monkey

A Komodo catches a monkey but doesn’t want to share it with his friend, so he runs off in a jiffy to eat it alone. I’m not sure the other Komodo is going to agree with this. I didn’t know dragons were so selfish. I always see them share dinners together. This monkey hits the jackpot when four dragons are vying for its attention. The only problem is they’re all starving and want a piece of him.  Monkeys that fall from trees are swallowed by Komodos. The Komodo dragon ambushed and swallowed one of the monkeys who fell while struggling for the territory. It’s unfortunate for the monkey, but I guess that’s how the wheel of life turns.

snippet.title: Wendy's All-You-Can-Eat Superbar Commercial w/ Dave Thomas, 1995
snippet.description:
Back in the 80s, and even the early 90s, a lot of fast food restaurants had salad bars, or 'fixins bars', where you could pile as many pickles on your hamburger as you pleased. For one low price, you could even build your own salad... or just sit with someone else and make a salad for free like my grandmother did from the bounty of free vegetables and sides laid out.

Unfortunately, that trend came to an end for a variety of reasons, as America's right to free pickles slowly dies.

Uploaded here because every Dave Thomas commercial deserves a place of honor in history, and I don't think this one has been uploaded yet.

Recorded October 1995.
=============
For more unusual, lost, obscure, and forgotten media, please check out http://www.mindlessshelfindulgence.com
